warmth /wɔːmθ/

1. N-UNCOUNT The warmth of something is the heat that it has or produces. 温暖 

例： She went further into the room, drawn by the warmth of the fire. 她被火的温暖吸引着，走进了房间。 

2. N-UNCOUNT The warmth of something such as a garment or blanket is the protection that it gives you against the cold. 保暖 

例： The blanket will provide additional warmth and comfort in bed. 毯子能让你睡觉时感觉更温暖更舒适。

